content.message: Are you a fan of Google or Microsoft?
Both are excellent technology they are helpful in many ways. For the security purpose both are super.
I'm not  a huge fan of Google, but I use it a lot because I have to. I think they are a monopoly in some sense.
Google provides online related services and products, which includes online ads, search engine and cloud computing.
Yeah, their services are good. I'm just not a fan of intrusive they can be on our personal lives.
Google is leading the alphabet subsidiary and will continue to be the Umbrella company for Alphabet internet interest.
Did you know Google had hundreds of live goats to cut the grass in the past?
It is very interesting. Google provide "Chrome OS" which is a light weight OS. Google provided a lot of hardware mainly in 2010 to 2015.
I like Google Chrome. Do you use it as well for your browser?
Yes.Google is the biggest search engine and Google service figure out top 100 website, including Youtube and Blogger.
By the way, do you like Fish?
Yes. They form a sister group of tourniquets- they make the sea water clean and remove the dust from it. Fish is the biggest part in the eco-system.
Did you know that a seahorse is the only fish to have a neck?
Freshwater fish only drink water through the skin via Osmosis, Saltwater fish drink water through the mouth. Dolphins are friendly to human beings.
Interesting, they also have gills. Did you know that jellyfish are immortal?
Yes. Fish is the important resources of human world wide for the commercial and subsistence fish hunts the fish in the wild fisheries.
What about cats, do you like cats? I'm a dog fan myself.
The cat is referred as domestic cat and wild cat. They make our world very clean from rats!
Yeah, cats can be cool, but they sure do spend a lot of their time sleeping.
Cats hear the sounds too faint or too high frequency human ears can hear.
I heard that too. Well, it was nice chatting with you. Have a good day.
do you like dance?
Yes  I do. Did you know Bruce Lee was a cha cha dancer?
Yes he even won a hardcore cha cha championship in 1958
Yeah. Did you know Tupac was a ballet dancer?
Yes and he even was in the production of the nutcracker
Yeah. Ballet dancer go through 4 pairs of shoes a week
Yes that is a lot of shoes and also a lot of money
Yeah true. Did you know babies are really good at dancing?
Yes and they smile more when they hit the beat
Yeah they are much smarter than we give them credit for
True Did you know Jackson had a patent on a dancing device?
Yes it helped him smooth out his dance moves
Nice. Do you like Shakespeare?
Yes I do. Do you know that he popularized many phrases
Yes like good riddance, in my heart of hearts and such
Yes and then he also invented names like Jessica, Olivia and Miranda
Yes. And for his works you have to use old english for it to make sense
Yes otherwise the rhymes and puns do not seem to work out
Yes. He lived at the same time as Pocahontas too
I wonder if they met how that would go from there
Yeah interesting point. Nice chat
Hey what's up do use Google very often?I really love the company and was surprised to hear that it was founded back in 1998.
i think everyone must use it daily! its become ingrained in every day life
Agreed. The Google headquarters in Mountain View California is nicknamed the Google Plex.
thats funny. The current CEO is Sundar Pichai, i didnt know Larry Page was replaced
Oh yeah I didn't know that either. I also want to go to google Plex to see the goats who mow their lawn by eating it.
say what now?? they have that??
Yeah apparently lol! They do that instead of hiring people to mow!
thats both funny and i guess imaginative. leave it to a huge tech company to employ actual goats!
Yeah exactly I am sure they are cheaper. One thing I bet they couldn't exploit is fish. I think fish are so cool there is actually a breed of jellyfish that is immortal.
i had rememered hearing about that before. Immortatlity is wasted on a jellyfish haha. did you know a seahorse is the only fish that has an actual neck?
That is so funny I guess I never considered a seahorse a fish. The black swallower fish sounds a lot like a snake because it can eat pray that is so large.
i guess they live up to their name then!
It seems they do. I also didn't know that there was a difference with how freshwater and saltwater fish drink.
thats crazy. i wonder why fresh water ones only use osmosis?
Yeah and saltwater fish are lucky because they can do that and drink through their mouth's.
seems like fresh water fish got the short end of the stick with that one. Have you ever been to a cat cafe?
I have never been to a cat cafe no, what about you? Seems like they are popular in Japan and Taiwan.
no but I would love to! paying hourly to hang out with adorable cats? im in!
Yeah that would be a lot of fun. I didn't realize that cats sleep so much. Must be nice.
i guess thats where the phrase "cat nap" comes from
Oh yeah I guess so ha ha. There's even a town in Alaska that has a mayor cat.
Hello, do you follow tennis?
Not really. I just know each player uses a strung racket and they hit a hollow ball.
Did you know Polo shirts were originally invented for tennis?
I did know. I know Lacoste shirts had the crocodile and it was a symbol for Rene "the crocodile" lacoste who was a famous player.
Yep. A black man won the first US open tennis title back in 1968 and no black man has won it since.
Wow! Over 50 years and still holding the record! I think the next year in 1969 they used a helicopter to dry the grass tennis courts for the US open.
I agree. They used a helicopter to dry the grass tennis courts for the 1969 US open.
Yes, they did. The longest tennis match went on for 11 hours over three days. I bet they were exhausted!
That's crazy long!
I agree! It's amazing the facts you can find on Google. Did you know that a single Google search requires more computing power than it took to send Neil Armstrong to the moon?
That's pretty amazing! I saw that Google maps calculates traffic by how fast Android devices are moving on the road.
I never knew that! I wonder whose? I know I heard that back in the day Google used goats to keep the lawn under control instead of hiring people to mow.
That's hilarious! Google went down for 5 minutes back in 2013 and took 40% of the web traffic with it.
I can imagine. I use it a lot. It's hard to believe its only been around since 1998.
I agree. When there is a dispute on a border, Google maps tailors the map to the claims of each country where the internet browser is located.
That sounds logical. I wish I would have gotten on board with the 2004 initial public offering to buy stock. I can't even imagine the outcome.
I can't either. Do you like shoes?
I love shoes!! I know that shoes made 5000 years ago perform better than today's shoes!
That's pretty amazing they perform better than the shoes of today!
I agree. I can't see how though. I find it amazing the array of choices like ones that can cost thousands of dollars a pair.
It was good chatting with you!
Hello do you like tennis?
Yes. Tennis is a racket sport that can be played individually against a single opponent or doubles.
Yes,  thanks for the explaination.  Did you know that polo shirts were made originally for tennis players?
Yes, It is more comfortable to wear while playing, and it also make the popular of the shirts.
They used a helicopter to dry the grass in the 1969 us open lol
In 19th century, modern tennis is originated in England as Lawn tennis.
Nice,  sounds fun!  The longest tennis match went on for 3 days!  can you imagine?
When this match happened ?
I think around 2015
Thanks. The main component of tennis is racket until 1978 a tennis player was allowed to use absolutely any object as racket.
Thats interesting!
Google was founded in 1998. It is an American multinational technology company that is specialized in internet-related services.
Seems like a long time ago even though it wasnt.
It is the biggest search engine and cloud computing service. It also many application like gmail, youtube, etc...
Yes,  I recently read that a google search requires more computing power than it took to send astronauts to the moon lol
Google is the most valuable brand in 2017. Google announced the new company called Calico.
wow awesome.  Instead of hiring people to mow the lawn,  they hired goats.
The company moved to mobile android system the Chrome OS is the light weight operating system.
ok.  I recently read that they calculate the taffic by how fast android phones are moving.
It is very interesting thing. Technology are used to identify were are we. It affect the privacy of person.
I agree.  Its been good chatting.
Do you like tennis? I just love to play the sport.
I've played it a couple time in high school gym class, I wasn't that good
i love it! Tennis is a racket sport that can be played individually against a single opponent or in teams
I watch it sometimes when Serena Williams is playing
yeah i like to watch her play. Polo shirts were originally invented for tennis by famous player rene "the crocodile" lacoste. i love their colgne for men
Intresting, the longest match played in a polo shirt was 22 hours
yeah if i recall it went over three days or so
That's a long time, I don't think I've ever done anything for 3 days straight
im not sure if its true but Us open quarterfinalist gael monfils beat the "roger federer of paddle tennis" after learning how to play just days earlier.
Man that's crazy, almost as crazy as using a helicopter to dry grass tennis courts
yeah i have heard that as well and though it sounded really dangerous. i wonder if their were people in the crowd?
I hope not, if I was there I'd be cold
yeah. In 1998, serena and venus williams said they could beat any man ranked 200 or worse in a game of tennis. they lost when challenged twice lol
lol, well she did win the australian open when she was ranked 95th
i have heard Serena williams is a co-owner of the miami dolphins
I didn't know that, she speaks french and italian so I wonder if she owns any sports teams in Europe
not sure but In january 2007, serena williams was ranked 95th in the world in tennis
I never knew she was ever ranked that low
well she reached the No. 1 ranking for the first time on July 8, 2002 but has since fallen
Wow, shes so good though, she won a grand slam while pregnant
I guess in my opinion her and her sister are kinda overated.
I don't know, maybe
Have you heard of the new "First Man" film starring Ryan Gosling?
No, I have not.  Please tell me about it.
It's a space movie.  He plays the character of Neil Armstrong.  It was released Friday.
Did you watch the movie?  Was it really a space movie?
I haven't seen it yet.  Today was the first time I heard of it.
It is hard to talk about this movie if we both have not seen it.  Can we change the topic?
Let's talk about Earth.  It's the third planet from the sun.
Apparently, 80 percent of the earth's natural forests have already been destroyed.  It's depressing to me.
That is sad for sure.  Sad that people are the cause of it too.
When the earth was first formed, there was only 5.5 hours long in a day.
Wow.  I didn't know that.  71 percent of the earth's surface is covered by water.  I wonder what covers the polar regions?
Ice?  I am not sure though.  Apparently, earth will be helium free by the end of the 21st century.
Yes.  Ice is right.  It's almost like the history of the earth is like watching a science fiction movie only in real life.
I like science fiction.  I like to imagine things, like aliens in a different planet.
Do you like Starship Troopers?
Yes, because it is the only science fiction novel recommended by three branches of the military.  I wonder why they recommended it though - do you know?
I have no idea.  lol  The word robotics was made up by a book writer - Isaac Asimov.  Seems like robots and space are always a big theme for science fiction books and movies.
By the way, do you know that the United Nations appointed an ambassador to greet extraterrestrials in case they want to say hello to us?
That's interesting!  What a job to have!  That's just like something out of the movie Star Wars, which came out in 1977 and the value of that franchise is now $65 billion dollar!
Wow.  That is a lot of money.  I heard that it is currently the 5th largest grossing media franchise.
Initially 20th century fox was convinced that Star Wars was going to be a flop.  Wow we're they wrong.
They were wrong indeed.  George Lucas got a better deal by forgoing $500k directing fee.
James Earl Jones only made $7,500 for 2 1/2 hours of work providing the voice for Darth Vader.  Thought he would have spent more time and made more money recording that voice.
I do not think $7500 is a lot of money to provide Darth Vader's voice because the movie was very successful.  What do you think?
I wonder if the actors get any royalties from the movie?
They should.  George Lucas should be generous since he got so much money from Star Wars.
You would think!  He's a billionaire from the movie!
Rich people are often cheap.
That's sad...but so true.  I've seen it too much during my working lifetime where the people at the top get richer and the workers on the factory floor just barely have enough money to live on.
I wonder if someone was fired at fox because of George Lucas deal. Anyway, I've got to run.  Nice chatting with you.
Dogs or cats?
Hi! I have two cats, but want a dog. You?
I like dogs more, but dont mind cats! Google likes dogs more though
Hah. I see their code of conduct state they are a DOG company.
lol, I heard you can bring you dog to work while working there, kind of discriminating against cats though!
Kinda odd since dogs are normally louder and more likely to poop somewhere. Looks like Istanbul even has vending machines to release food and water for strays.
that is a great point! The US needs to get those vending machines, I would donate so many plastic bottles. That is nice of that country
I wonder where else the dogs go if not for vencing machines?
right, they probably go for trash cans unfortunately. Did you know dogs have 12 types of blood?
Makes sense for variety. Apparently they have doggie blood drives too!
that would be so awesome to volunteer at. I will have to look them up. Did you know dogs and elephants are the only animals that respond to pointing, sorry cats
My cats responding to pointing, and throwing.
That is true, so I wonder if there are more we don't know about lol. Do you like horses at all?
I took a horse ride once and live in an area with lots of horses. They are beautiful animals. you?
They are so beautiful, I like petting them but never rode one. I wouldn't ride Icelandic horses because they are super fast.
I wonder if riders trained horses to do that?
I am sure they did. I just wouldn't ride horses to school on no vehicle day and get suspended like two students did. I feel that was pointless
That's funny and rather stupid at the same time.
For sure lol, it was so nice talking with you, say hi to your cats for me!
My cats will run away, but sure!
lol! bye now!
Crazy that early humans used to have to battle giant sloths! Who would've thought?
I know right! Humans have been around for a long time apparently I mean we lost our body hair 240,000 years ago!
Yea that's really interesting. I never knew humans could regrow a rib bone that has been surgically shortened, either.
No I didn't know that either. I wonder if other animals can do that? Like can we Harvest Pig ribs for food and then they will regrow that way we don't have to kill the pig haha

That would be awesome! I'm sure science will figure that out someday! We can already use our current technology to date the extinction of ground sloths and determine where ancient human footprints led to.
That's really cool. I would love to see that. They should put that in the movie! I think it's cool that humans are adapted for persistence running. We are some of the best animals in the world at it

Haha yea that would be cool. That's really surprising humans are the best at persistence running! I wouldn't have guessed that. As long as those pesky hiccups don't attack while running! Darn evolution leftovers!
Haha yep hiccups are so annoying! So is that frequency that causes fear in humans ,have you heard about that LOL?
No, I had not. So fear comes from sound...? I thought it had to do with the autonomic nervous system, fight or flight thing? That would be really interesting to look into further.
Can come from sound. And yes I'm going to look into that further as well. Do you like any animals by the way?
I used to own two cats, no current pets though. I would love to go to Japan and play with some cats at a cat cafe though! haha
Haha that does seem like a great idea! Get a drink and pet a cat LOL. Did you know that a cat will spend 10 years of its life sleeping when it's only 15 years old LOL that's a long time
That is nuts! What I wouldn't give to trade places! Or trade places with Stubbs, the cat who is the mayor of Talkeentna, Alaska! Sounds like a sweet gig.
It does sound awesome! I don't know what kind of work she does but she must be doing a great job lol have you ever seen the movie The Godfather by the way
Right? Haha And yea I've seen the Godfather but it's been a while.
Well in the opening scene the cat that they use, I don't know if you remember that part, but it was actually a stray apparently

Yea, I vaguely remember, that's awesome. Another sweet gig for a cat! Now if only I woulda thought to have one of my cats coauthor a book with me. I guess some physicist did so so that he could use the first person plural without being criticized!
That is funny! What do you think about Scotland putting a lot in place to protect the Loch Ness monster? Do you think that means he might exist LOL

Haha that is strange. It definitely makes one wonder...maybe the loch ness is some super secret scientific experiment or military weapon? Haha I guess thanks to the Germans, who in 2002 were the first to give animals constitutionally guaranteed legal rights, Scotland can do what it wants concerning the Loch Ness!
The Loch Ness monster should have legal rights to! Did you know that there are 20 quintillion individual animals on planet Earth. I have no idea how many zeros that is but I know it is a lot LOL
Haha that is insane. How does anyone even figure out that there's that many animals?! Interesting that domesticated animals develop a white patch on their forehead. I wonder what that's about?
I know right. like will a fish get a patch of white on its forehead?the only animals that have that that I've ever seen our dogs, so I just don't know LOL
Hi, Do you like to cook?
I love to cook. just not in july when it is so hot.
Right, it's no fun when it is hot and you're trying to cook. We like to grill a lot outside, which helps not make our home more hot.
Grilling out is the best to help with the heat inside the house. If I have to cook in the house i do it early in the morning before it gets too hot.
Yes that's another great idea. We also sometimes eat out if it is way too hot, or eating something like salads or cereal. Where we aren't using heat at all.
That is a great idea. We tend to eat leftovers too and just use the micorwave.
The microwave is great and fast, I agree. Making Icecream is a great way to cool down when it gets too hot. We also tend to use box fans.
We use a fan for sure. Also started using like a slow cooker or toaster oven not as hot and now can fit up to a whole chicken.
Great appliances help to cook! We love our air-fryer. Though it tends to eat up the area some, so we open the doors and dim the lights to help with the heat.
I heard some people turn their wrist upside down  to get their blood flowing to stay cool.
Wow great information, I will have to try that sometime. Do you like to eat fish or even go fishing?
I love to fish. the oldest goldfish lived to be 43 years old
Wow that is a long life for a goldfish! I like to go crabbing too. I heard the seahorse is the only fish with a neck, I
THere was a koi fish that lived 226 years
Whoa! That is crazy to know and interesting. I know there is a breed of jellyfish that is immortal.
Cool the barreleye fish has a transparent head.
Awesome. I heard that saltwater fish dink water through their mouths and through their skin, while a freshwater fish only drinks through their skin. Fish are fascinating.
That is pretty cool. Do you like to bird watch?
There are times when i Do like to look at the birds, how about you? Did you know that birds bones are really hollow. So hollow in fact that their skeleton weighs less than their feathers.
thats neat. They have then thousand living species.
That's cool. Some birds are known to fly from Alaska to mexico without sleeping, that is tiring to think about.
o wow. I wonder how many days that takes. Scientist say birds have regional accents.
That is cool how they even have accents like humans. My favorite is the hummingbird, they are tiny sometimes about 2 inches long.
They are the smallest birds and the ostrich is the biggest. Some birds don't fly.
This reminds me of the extinct dodo bird. They were actually a sub-family of pigeons.
pigeons are one of 3 birds that produce milk for their young.
Very cool. Pigeons are very pretty birds.
